From 60a7a37781a31ce1320952f20a8ae7dd41dcfce8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sankalp <sankalphimself@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 2026 17:02:48 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix(ci): resolve migration version 003 duplicate in CI
 pipeline

The CI pipeline was failing due to leftover __pycache__ files from the deleted
migration 003_add_consultation_type.py. Although the .py file was removed, the
.pyc cache files remained in __pycache__, causing a UNIQUE constraint violation
when the migration system attempted to discover migrations.

Changes:
- Clear __pycache__ directory in migrations/ to remove stale .pyc files
- Update server/.gitignore to explicitly exclude __pycache__ and .pyc files

This ensures clean migration discovery with only the current 6 migrations,
each with unique version numbers (001-006).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 server/.gitignore | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/server/.gitignore b/server/.gitignore
index db676c6..5536983 100644
--- a/server/.gitignore
+++ b/server/.gitignore
@@ -1,2 +1,7 @@
 cloudkit_data/
 .env
+__pycache__/
+*.pyc
+*.pyo
+*.pyd
+.Python
-- 
2.34.1


